FBIS4-11421 "drlat082_a_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-082 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Minister Named Small Island Organization Official Minister Named Small Island Organization Official FL2604184994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 GMT 26 Apr 94 FL2604184994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] On 26 April, Cuban Minister Rosa Elena Simeon has been designated vice president of the main committee of the First International Conference of Small Island Nations on Sustainable Development, which is being held in Bridgetown. Simeon told PRENSA LATINA that the appointment is an acknowledgment of Cuba's efforts in this field. The conference will reach its peak on 5-6 May, when it will hold meetings by state and government leaders of the alliance of island nations.
